stories.text:
I run a small company which works exclusively with early stage startups for their product development needs - in addition to building our own products.

Since working in a niche like that is a departure from routine software outsourcing, some people I talked to described my company as a startup studio or venture studio. BUT... venture studios don't work for clients.

This is more of a semantic thing than anything else, but can I call my company a "Venture Studio"?
stories.title: Can I call my company a “Venture Studio” if I also work with clients?
